BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bLt7NlRmaoxs_wb8D1GvU
SUMMARY:Journaling the Garden
DTSTAMP:20260327T064335Z
DTSTART:20260404T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Nature journaling at the Bellevue Botanical Garden is a wonderf
	ul way to connect with the environment through curiosity and observation o
	f the natural world. This free adult program will help guide your practice
	 whether you are just starting out or are an experienced journaler. In thi
	s warm and welcoming environment\, you will be encouraged to experiment an
	d find your voice. In each session we will gather for introductions and br
	ief guidance\, and then head out into Garden to journal and come back toge
	ther to share experiences.   \n\nPlease bring a dedicated journal and some
	thing to write with. We will meet at 9am the first Saturday of January-Nov
	ember 2026. Registration is recommended but not required.  \n\nThis free a
	dult program is facilitated by Anne Dziok\, Adult Education Program Manage
	r. Anne is a practicing multi-media artist who shows her work regionally. 
	   \n\nEmail us  with questions.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/
	details/journaling-the-garden/17658183/2026-04-04T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sp
	orts & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/journaling-the-garden/176
	58183/2026-04-04T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
